Node Js dependency pkg installation 

npm init - to create package.json file it will ask some info like name of project etc // project configuration
npm install express --save (will save this dependency in package.json)
npm install nano --save
npm install body-parser 
npm install errorhandler --save(For handling errors)
npm install url --save
npm install serve-favicon --save
npm install logger --save 
npm install json --save
npm install express-session --save
npm install -g nodemon  ---(use nodmon server.js) monitor any changes in server.js file (restart the server)
npm install morgan --save (HTTP request logger middleware for node.js)
npm install mongoose --save (db interaction)
	to connect to db = mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost:27017/test', {useNewUrlParser: true}); 


Morgan: is another HTTP request logger middleware for Node.js. It simplifies the process of logging requests to your application. You might think of Morgan as a helper that collects logs from your server, such as your request logs. It saves developers time because they donâ€™t have to manually create common logs. It standardizes and automatically creates request logs.

